It encapsulates a request as an object, which decouples the sender of the request 
  from the receiver and allowing flexible execution of operations.
It turns a request into object so that it can be passed, stored, queued or undone easily.
Encapsulates the request as an object and decouples the sender from receiver.

Ex:
A remote contorller-- user sends command like turining on lights, TV, AC, etc. 
 The remote doesnot directly control the devices instead, it passes command objects to them. Each device then executes the 
 the command independently, keeping the sender and receiver loosely coupled.

 REMOTE CONTROLLER-- COMMAND-->LIGHT 
                  --COMMAND-->TV 
                  --COMMAND-->SPEAKERS

Components:
Command Interface: Declares the common method for all commands.
Concrete Commands: Implement the interface and encapsulates specific actions
Invoker: Initiates the command execution without knowing the details
Receiver:Performs the actual operation defined by the command.                  
